c c KNOWN-LIMITATION regression: faithful --compile of this CNF emits a circuit
c c whose model count + model SET are correct (5897, matches brute force) but
c c which violates strict d-DNNF decomposability: some AND node has two
c c children whose subtrees both mention var 16. Root cause: conflict-learned
c c (redundant) clauses can bridge variables that CompAnalyzer placed in
c c different sub-components (the analyzer only sees irreducible clauses).
c c Propagation inside one sub-component then sets a variable that "belongs"
c c to another sub-component, which leaks into the OR's arc-lits.
c c
c c Test fixed at the count level only; --check-decomposable is intentionally
c c omitted because it currently fails. See git log for the deeper diagnosis.
c c Originally surfaced by `python3 tests/ddnnf_fuzz.py 500 --seed 207900131`.
c c
c c RUN: %solver --compile %t.nnf %s
c c RUN: %ddnnf_verify %t.nnf --cnf %s
p cnf 16 40
